## Why This Is Asked
Tests understanding of closures, promises, and memoization in a practical frontend pattern.

## Key Concepts
- Closures and encapsulation
- In-flight deduping of promises
- TTL caching and cleanup
- ES6 features: Map, arrow functions, async/await
- Testing approaches for async caches

## Code Example
```javascript
function createDataLoader(fetchFn) {
  const cache = new Map();
  const TTL = 60_000;
  const now = () => Date.now();
  function cleanup() {
    const t = now();
    for (const [k, v] of cache) {
      if (t - v.ts >= TTL) cache.delete(k);
    }
  }
  setInterval(cleanup, TTL);
  return {
    load(id) {
      const entry = cache.get(id);
      if (entry && (now() - entry.ts) < TTL) return entry.promise;
      const p = Promise.resolve(fetchFn(id)).finally(() => {});
      cache.set(id, { promise: p, ts: now() });
      return p;
    },
    clear(id){ cache.delete(id); },
    clearAll(){ cache.clear(); }
  };
}

// usage
const loader = createDataLoader((id)=> fetch(`/api/user/${id}`).then(r=>r.json()));
loader.load(123).then(console.log);
```

